{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σεμνός</b>,, ή, όν, <br /> (σέβομαι) <b>revered, august, holy</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> properly of gods, e.g. Demeter, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 1, 486; Hecate, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.79; Thetis, [prev. author] “N.” 5.25; Apollo, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 800; Poseidon, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 55; Pallas Athena, [prev. work] 1090 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; at Athens the Erinyes were specially the σεμναὶ θεαί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aj.” 837, “OC” 90, 458, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1312, “Th.” 224, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.126, Autocl. cited in 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1398b26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; or simply Σεμναί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 383 (Lyric poetry), 1041 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 410 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ σ. ὄνομα their name, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 41; σ. βάθρον the threshold of their temple, [prev. work] 100; σ. τέλη their rites, [prev. work] 1050 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of things divine, ὄργια σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 478, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 765; θέμεθλα δίκης 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 4.14; ὑγίεια 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 70; θυσία 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.42 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; σ. ἄντρον the cave of Cheiron, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “P.” 9.30, compare “O.” 5.18 \">Refs</a>]; σ. δόμος the temple of Apollo, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “N.” 1.72; παιάν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 393 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; σέλμα σ. ἡμένων, of the Olympian gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ag.” 183 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs</a>]; σ. ἔργα, of the gods, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Supp.” 1037 (Lyric poetry); μυστήρια 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 804, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 25; τέρμων οὐρανοῦ [prev. work] 746 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. βίος <b>devoted to the gods</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ion” 56 \">Refs</a>]; σεμνὰ φθέγγεσθαι, ={εὔφημα}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 109 (variant), compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 315, 364 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἦ πού τι σ. ἔστιν ὃ ξυναμπέχει; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 521 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ σ. <b>holiness</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.126. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of human or half-human beings, <b>reverend, august</b>, ἐν θρόνῳ σεμνῷ σεμνὸν θωκέοντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.173, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 975, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 384, +others; σ. θάλος Ἀλκαϊδᾶν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.68; τὸ σχῆμα σεμνὸς κοὐ ταπεινός 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 688 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ φαυλότεραι.. παρὰ τὰς σεμνὰς καθεδοῦνται beside <b>the great ladies</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 617, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.42; οἱ σεμνότατοι ἐν ταῖς πόλεσιν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 257d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄνθρωπος οὐ σ., i.e. a nobody, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 52D. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to χαῦνος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 227b (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to κομψός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 8.19; σεμνὸς οὐ προσώπου συναγωγαῖς ἀλλὰ βίου κατασκευαῖς 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 9.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i>, <b>revered by.. </b>, σ. πόλει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Riv.Fil.” 57.379 (from Crete)\">Refs</a>]; also, <b>worthy of respect, honourable</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Tim.3.8, 11, NT.Phil.4.8. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of human things, <b>august, stately, majestic</b>, θᾶκοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 519; ἱμάτια 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 940, compare “Ra.” 1061 (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ταφή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.3.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πράγματα, ἔργα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1472, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.213; σεμνοτέραν τὴν πόλιν ποιῆσαι 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 5.45; οἰκία τοῦ γείτονος οὐδὲν σεμνοτέρα 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.26, compare 29; ψεύδεσι [τοῦ Ὁμήρου] σ. ἔπεστί τι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.22; λεγόντων.. περὶ αὐτοῦ σ. λόγους 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Tragedy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 502b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of style, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Poetica” 1458a21, compare “Rh.” 1404b8 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (<i>comparative</i>); of certain metres, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 1408b32 \">Refs</a>]; ἐπὶ τὸ σ. μιμεῖσθαι to imitate it in its <b>noble qualities</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 814e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι λέγειν, πράσσειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “R.” 382b, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 447; σεμνὰ ἄττα μεμαθηκότας 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epistulae” 342a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν σ. nothing <b>very wonderful</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1146a15 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; so τί ἂν εἴη τὸ σ. (i.e. τοῦ νοῦ); [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Metaphorical” 1074b18 \">Refs</a>]; <b>worthy of respect</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 996 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σεμνόν ἐστι, with <i>infinitive</i>, 'tis a <b>noble, fine</b> thing to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 392a, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator “Epistulae” 9.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, σ. βρῶμα a <b>noble</b> dish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristopho Comicus 7, compare 4th c.BC: Archestratus Epicus “fragment” 20; σ. ὀσμή 4th c.BC: Mnesimachus Comicus 4.60, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in bad sense, <b>proud, haughty</b>, τὰ σέμν᾽ ἔπη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1107; σεμνότερος καὶ φοβερώτερος 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ σ. <b>haughty reserve</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 93, compare “Med.” 216. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> in contempt or irony, <b>solemn, pompous</b>, σ. καὶ ἅγιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 249a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί σεμνὸν καὶ πεφροντικὸς βλέπει; look <b>grave and solemn</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 773; τὸ σ. ἄγαν καὶ τραγικόν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1406b7: very frequently in Comedy texts, ἀνελκτοῖς ὀφρύσι σεμνός 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 355 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὡς σ. οὑπίτριπτος how <b>grand</b> the rascal is! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 275; ὡς σ. ὁ κατάρατος [prev. author] “Ra.” 178 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λόγοι σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “V.” 1175; σεμνὸς σεμνῶς χλανίδ᾽ ἕλκων 4th c.BC: Ephippus Comicus 19. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> <b>-νῶς</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 193, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1133, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 585, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὥσπερ κοχλίας σεμνῶς ἐπηρκὼς τὰς ὀφρῦς, of Plato, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Amphis Comicus 13; σεμνῶς κεκοσμημένος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.1.6, etc.; περὶ εὐτελῶν σ. λέγειν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1408a13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-ότερον</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.5.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-ότατα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.31.7. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4586","accentedUnicode":"σεμνός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4576","matchingForm":"σέβομαι","stepTransliteration":"sebomai","gloss":"be devout","_zh_tw_Gloss":"拜","_es_Gloss":"ser devoto","_zh_Gloss":"拜"},{"strongNumber":"G4585","matchingForm":"σεμίδαλις","stepTransliteration":"semidalis","gloss":"fine flour","_zh_tw_Gloss":"細麵","_es_Gloss":"harina refinada","_zh_Gloss":"细面"}],"shortDef":"worthy of respect, noble","mediumDef":"worthy of respect, noble <br /><b>august, venerable; honorable, reputable, worthy of respect</b> <ref='Php.4.8'>Phil. 4:8;</ref> <b>grave, serious, dignified,</b> <ref='1Ti.3.8, 11'>1Tim. 3:8, 11</ref>; <ref='Tit.2.2'>Tit. 2:2</ref>*","stepGloss":"noble","stepTransliteration":"semnos","count":4,"_es_Definition":"serio ; de buen carácter, honorable, digno, respetable","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (指人) 有威嚴的, 崇高的, 可尊敬的<br>2) (指品格) 高尚正直, 無可指摘, 聖潔 (腓 4:8)","_zh_Definition":"1) (指人) 有威严的, 崇高的, 可尊敬的<br>2) (指品格) 高尚正直, 无可指摘, 圣洁 (腓 4:8)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"khả kính ; Được tôn kính. Đáng kính, tôn trọng, nghiêm trang, nghiêm túc, đáng trọng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要端莊, 可敬","_es_Gloss":"noble","_zh_Gloss":"要端庄, 可敬"}]}